President Donald Trump has announced his intention to nominate Kathleen Troia McFarland as the United States Ambassador to the Republic of Singapore. McFarland currently serves as Assistant to the President and Deputy National Security Advisor. She has extensive experience in national security and has provided analysis for Fox News. McFarland has previously served in the Nixon, Ford, and Reagan administrations on the National Security Council and in the Department of Defense. Lieutenant General H.R. McMaster, President Trump's National Security Advisor, praised McFarland's leadership during the transition and stated that she initiated the first strategic policy reviews for the NSC. McFarland expressed her honor at being trusted by President Trump and her excitement to implement his policies with one of America's key allies in Asia. Dr. Rick Waddell has been appointed as McFarland's successor at the NSC. Dr. Waddell is a Major General in the U.S. Army Reserve and has served in Iraq and Afghanistan. He holds a PhD in International Relations from Columbia, an MA in History and Portuguese from Oxford, and a BS from West Point.